<h3 class="title">Fall Party For Paws &ndash; A Festival of Food Nov. 19</h3>
<div class="article">
  <p class="date">November 4, 2011</p>
  <p class="publication">The Herald-Chronicle</p>
  <div class="article-text">
   <p>The fall &quot;Party for Paws&quot; will be held on Saturday, Nov. 19 from 6-8:30 p.m. at the Sewanee Inn on University Ave. in Sewanee. This party and silent auction will benefi t the Franklin County Humane Society and their shelter, Animal Harbor.</p>
    <p>The event includes a festival of food generously donated by IvyWild Sewanee, Julia's Fine Foods, Lorena's, Modern Dave's Café, Natural Bridge Events, Shenanigans, The Blue Chair and The Edgeworth Inn. Enjoy a feast of hors d’oeuvres and wines, beers and mixed drinks and the chance to bid on a selection of works by local artists and artisans, antiques, memorabilia and other goods and services &ndash; and good company in a good cause.</p>
    <p>Tickets are $30 each available from Animal Care Center (967-6345), Town and Country Veterinary Hospital (967-3666), Bubbles and Bows (967-9397), Animal Harbor (962-4472), Jim Curty, Citizens Community Bank (967-3342), Carolyn Maher (962-9750), Cecelia Brodioi (967-2065), Paula Reed (967-3521), Sue Ridyard (sridyard@sewanee.edu or 598-9260), Pat Thompson (pthompson313@gmail.com or 598-1657), Susan Rupert (srupert@sewanee edu or 967-8903).</p>
    <p>The proceeds from this event will be used by Animal Harbor to rescue, care for and re-home companion animals. </p>
